bug.short_desc: Table does not render HeaderCellRenderer right

long_desc.thetext:
When the table is rendered and you change the appearance of the header cell widget only the headers that were not rendered so far will get the new appearance.
This is because the table has a cache for the header cell widgets.

Added "headerCellRendererChanged" in Basic Columnmodel that will tricker a full update of the table (pane as well, as the column size could have changed because of the new appearance)
Fixed in trunk with Rev. 24038
Fixed a bug with event listeners in the pane.Model as well -> listeners were not added/ removed when a new table column model was set
Fixed bug in branch 1.2.2 as well -> rev. 24039

Created attachment 846 Demo code
Added demo code for further testing.
To reproduce the initial bug. uncomment the line "this.fireDataEvent("headerCellRendererChanged", {col:col});" in the qx.ui.table.columnmodel.Basic.setHeaderCellRenderer function, so that the repainting of the table is not triggered anymore.
